tags Optimizers, Neural Network source https://ruder.io/optimizing-gradient-descent/index.html#adam An optimizer which effectively combines RMSProp and Momentum. The algorithm is as follows. Using the gradient \(g_t\), we compute moving averages (or decaying averages) of the first and second moments.
\begin{align*} m_t &amp;= \beta_m m_{t-1} + (1-beta_m) g_t \\ v_t &amp;= \beta_v v_{t-1} + (1-beta_v) g^2_t \end{align*}
Both of these estimated averages are biased towards zero, and thus to unbias these moving averages we scale by \(\frac{1}{1-\beta^t}\)
